10. Touching things. I see with my fingers. It's not even a texture thing, I just feel an innate need to touch things, even if I def should not be touching something.

9. Sensory overload. As I said before, I am hearing everything always so when there are like more than 3 loud noises (like music & phones) it stresses me out a lot & I either have to go be in silence or eliminate one of the noises

8. Patterns. I do this weird lil thing where I tap each of my fingers with my thumb & I have to do evenly. I alos used to be obsessive abt making sure I didn't step on the cracks on concrete. Also I must to walk instep w/ my music (but that could easily just be a band thing)
7. Con't: silly correlation but I am like always moving my feet/toes or popping my fingers
7. Fidgeting. I am always moving around or messing with something. Sometimes I don't even realize until it's been pointed out that I'm moving/messing w/ a body part or some random object obsessively
Forgot to mention that I have had multiple meltdowns bc I genuinely could not focus or retain knowledge no matter how hard I tried

6. Con't: the only way I can tune noises out is by listening to music. I rarely am able to do hw unless I'm listening to music bc that's the only way I can block out all the irrelevant noise. Music is a focused noise & it's helps me with focusing on my tasks

6. Noises. I am constantly hearing everything ALWAYS. I lack the ability to tune out unimportant noises. I'm always listening to my mvmt, others, fan noise, electrical noises, cars, anything & everything. I can usually count up to like 5-8 things I'm hearing at any given moment

5. Losing focus. Last Spring sem was rlly hard for me because I just couldnt focus on my school work at all. No matter how hard I tried, something would distract me & take away from my focus. Soemthing as small as mvmt around me would make me lose focus & stop doing work

4. Con't: actually I feel like this sorta goes hand-in-hand w/ forgetting things. Sometimes I'll be at target & see sumn cute & I'll go look at it for awhile & completely forget what was I was actually there for. In essence, I am very easily distracted always

4. Getting distracted. Obvi this is a big one. I don't really have much to say on this except that I was supposed to be watching a week overview for one of my classes & instead made this thread & took in NOTHING from the video LMAOOO

3. Con't: I will remind myself abt said lil tasks constantly & forget abt them for hours to days to weeks until I actually do it. Also the link between adhd & object permanence is very interesting & you should do some research abt it

3. Losing/forgetting things. I CONSTANTLY forget I have something as soon as it's out of my view. This happens A LOT when I eat & I have my drink off to the side & it's not in my vision. I forget abt lil tasks for long periods of time (I have wanted to clean my mirror for 2weeks)

2. Hyperfixation. This is big one tbh. I frequently go thru phases of being obsessed with a new object or article of clothing. It will be the ONLY thing I wear for like a week or 2 after I get it or until I find a new piece of clothing. This happens with food too, but not as much

1. Picking at my skin. I only recently realized this is a symptom fun fact! I am constantly picking at my skin, any blemish, bump, or dry skin is going to be messed with. I often pick at them to the point of bleeding until I realize I need to stop & I still pick at them later
